An Act relative to harm reduction and racial justice.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 1.
2 (a) Chapter 94C of the General Laws is hereby amended by striking out section 34, as so
3 appearing, and inserting in place thereof the following section:-
4 Section 34: No person knowingly or intentionally shall possess a controlled substance
5 unless such substance was obtained directly, or pursuant to a valid prescription or order,
6 from a practitioner while acting in the course of his professional practice, or except as otherwise
7 authorized by the provisions of this chapter. Except as provided in Section 32L of this Chapter,
8 any person who violates this section shall be subjected to receiving a written list of resources in
9 lieu of a citation\
